TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Class of Utility Functions Containing all the Common Utility Functions
AU  - Brockett, Patrick L.
AU  - Golden, Linda L.
Y1  - 1987/08/01
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.33.8.955
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.33.8.955
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 955
EP  - 964
VL  - 33
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper presents a class of utility functions (class A∞) that contains all of the utility functions commonly used for mathematical modeling: the class consisting of those utility functions whose derivatives alternate in sign. A simple representation via mixtures of exponential utilities is provided for this class which is both mathematically convenient and conducive to functional operations. A connection with Laplace transforms and the resultant implications for preference relations, aggregation and utility assessment are discussed.
AB  - This paper presents a class of utility functions (class A∞) that contains all of the utility functions commonly used for mathematical modeling: the class consisting of those utility functions whose derivatives alternate in sign. A simple representation via mixtures of exponential utilities is provided for this class which is both mathematically convenient and conducive to functional operations. A connection with Laplace transforms and the resultant implications for preference relations, aggregation and utility assessment are discussed.
