T1  - A Layout Planning System with Multiple Criteria and a Variable Domain Representation
AU  - Jacobs, F. Robert
Y1  - 1987/08/01
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.33.8.1020
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.33.8.1020
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1020
EP  - 1034
VL  - 33
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper describes a new system capable of solving detailed facility layout problems. The system allows the consideration of multiple objectives on the layout solution. Criteria related to weighted distance between interacting layout elements, the structure of the final layout design, the use of circulation space in the layout and the satisfaction of special adjacency requirements, are included in the formulation. The paper includes a comparison of this new procedure to existing procedures using problems selected from the literature.
AB  - This paper describes a new system capable of solving detailed facility layout problems. The system allows the consideration of multiple objectives on the layout solution. Criteria related to weighted distance between interacting layout elements, the structure of the final layout design, the use of circulation space in the layout and the satisfaction of special adjacency requirements, are included in the formulation. The paper includes a comparison of this new procedure to existing procedures using problems selected from the literature.
